<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-02-01T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-02-01T17:00:00-05:00" n="57" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d57">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">812.79614/–: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Geissler</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-02-01T17:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">February 1,
                                        1927—5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>7. Legation’s despatch No. 1391, dated January 19. Department desires
                            that you discreetly ascertain who is backing Parada financially.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
